   SABRE-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ In a move that could touch off
investor interest in airline stocks, AMR Corp. said Tuesday that it
would spin off its 83 percent stake in Sabre Holdings Corp., the
world's largest travel reservation company. By David J. Morrow.
</P>
<P>
   AWARDS-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ The One Club for Art and Copy,
whose 1,000 members include many of the best-known creative talents
on Madison Avenue, announced Tuesday its choices for the most
outstanding ads of the decade. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   PRODUCT-AS-PROCESS (Undated) _ Marshall McLuhan wrote 35 years
ago that the medium is the message. Today, a great many business
thinkers, in one way or another, seem to be saying something
similar: the process is the product. Puzzling or not, that thought
has become today's operating philosophy. Aside from electronic
gadgetry, the other things we buy _ the cars we drive, the shoes we
wear, the trips we take _ are not all that different from what they
were 10 years ago. But the ways they are produced have been
overhauled, as the awesome speed of the Internet forces every
business to reinvent its product as a process. By Fred Andrews.
</P>
