<P>
   NAVY-VIEQUES (Aboard the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower) _ The Navy
battle fleet led by this aircraft carrier wrapped up its combat
training for the Persian Gulf Wednesday. Senior commanders declare
the 16-ship armada ready for combat without the live-fire exercises
it has previously had on the Puerto Rican island of Vieques. The
officers say that since Vieques is now off-limits for such
exercises, their pilots and naval gunnery crews will get live-fire
training in Sardinia en route to the gulf. By STEWART M. POWELL.
