<HEADLINE>
HUGE BELL TO RING IN HOPES FOR PEACE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I heard France was giving Kentucky the largest bell ever
cast. Where's it going to go, and why? _ R.W.B., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The World Peace Bell is the largest free-swinging bell in the
world. It has been installed at Millennium Monument in Newport,
Ky., just across the Ohio River from Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   The bronze bell, which weighs 66,000 pounds and is 12 feet tall
and 12 feet wide, will be rung every hour on New Year's Eve to
promote peace in the 21st century. It was cast at the Paccard
Foundry in Annecy, France, and is owned by the Millennium Monument
Corp.
</P>
<P>
   The bell is decorated with designs representing the highlights
of the second millennium, including Einstein's Theory of
Relativity; man's first step on the moon; and the evolution of
communications technology, from the Gutenberg Press to the digital
chip.
</P>
<P>
   For more information on the bell, call (606) 655-9500 or visit
the Web site www.millenniummonument.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Whatever happened to Beverly Ann Archer, the actress who
played Iola on the TV series ``Mama's Family?'' _ Y.N., Chicago
</P>
<P>
   A: Archer continues to act, working last year on the soap
``Young and the Restless'' and the film ``Walking to the
Waterline.''
</P>
<P>
   After starring in the sitcoms ``Mama's Family'' and ``Major
Dad'' from 1986 to 1993, the 51-year-old actress appeared in ``The
Brady Bunch Movie'' and the TV films ``Project: ALF'' and
``Christmas Wish.''
</P>
<P>
   You can write to Archer in care of SBV, 145 S. Fairfax Ave.,
Suite 310, Los Angeles, CA 90036.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Several years ago, there was a store at The Parks at
Arlington mall called Units that sold the best pants I've ever
worn. Is the company still in business? _ C.S., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: In 1994, after five years of declining sales, J.C. Penney
closed all 113 Units stores.
</P>
<P>
   The Dallas apparel company Colesce Couture sells a similar
clothing line called Multitudes that was once marketed under the
name Multiples. The garments are sold by independent sales
representatives who also sell Colesce's line of lingerie. To find
one in your area, call sales administrator Barbara Murray at (214)
631-4860.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
