Doug Flutie knows football, and autism 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Doug Flutie of the Buffalo Bills? _
B.M., Millbury, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Flutie or anyone else affiliated with the team in
care of Buffalo Bills, One Bills Drive, Orchard Park, NY 14127.
</P>
<P>
   After learning in 1995 that their son has the neurological
disorder autism, Flutie and his wife, Laurie, established the Doug
Flutie Jr. Foundation for Autism to assist affected children and
their parents.
</P>
<P>
   If you're contacting Flutie to make a donation, send it to Doug
Flutie Jr. Foundation for Autism, Giving Back Fund, 54 Canal St.,
Suite 320, Boston, MA 02114.
</P>
<P>
   The charity's Web site is www.dougflutie.org.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I heard a weatherperson say that dew point meant the
percentage of moisture in the air. I thought that was humidity.
What's the difference? _ J.D.J., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Both measurements describe the moistness in the air, but they
track it in different ways.
</P>
<P>
   Dew point is the temperature to which air must cool for its
moisture to condense and form dew. Humidity, more accurately called
relative humidity, is the percentage of moisture in the air.
Humidity reaches 100 percent when the air contains all the water
vapor it can possibly hold.
</P>
<P>
   The dew point of air increases rapidly as humidity increases and
is often used as part of a ``discomfort index.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find a distributor for Magnalite pots and pans? _
L.D., North Richland Hills, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The company that has sold Magnalite in recent years,
WagnerWare of Sidney, Ohio, recently closed its doors and is in
negotiations with a new buyer.
</P>
<P>
   An Internet retailer, Professional Cookware to Go, sells
Magnalite and has a few items left from when WagnerWare was in
business. For ordering information, call (877) 537-5468 or visit
the Web site www.procookware.com.
</P>
<P>
   Professional Cookware has heard from a few customers who found
Magnalite items at Wal-Mart, Service Merchandise, Ace Hardware and
other hardware stores.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
