corruption scandal. By Todd S. Purdum.
</P>
<P>
   NY-TRANSIT (New York) _ The tentative contract that the transit
workers' union reached early Wednesday calls for an 18 percent
increase in take-home pay over three years, giving New York City's
subway and bus workers the largest wage increase received by the
city's public-sector workers in more than a decade. By Steven
Greenhouse.
</P>
