   ENTERTAINMENT
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``e'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   COLUMBIA-APPOINT (Hollywood) _ Sony Pictures Entertainment,
whose motion picture division is coming off a terrible six months
that has seen a string of high-profile flops and not a sizable hit
since early summer's ``Big Daddy,'' has decided to promote the
president of its movie-making division, Columbia Pictures' Amy
Pascal, to the post of chairman of Columbia. Sony Pictures chairman
John Calley _ Ms. Pascal's boss _ said that the title change, which
had been widely predicted and made official on Wednesday, was done
mainly to clarify Ms. Pascal's position in the company. She remains
the key person at Columbia. By Rick Lyman.
</P>
