<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE BUSINESS BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These business stories for release Thursday, December 16, 1999,
are moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the financial (f) category. Stories also
moving in lifestyle will be marked with (f, l).
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-BOARD _ ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola board members meet Wednesday,
the first time they have done so since Chairman and Chief Executive
Officer M. Douglas Ivester announced he was stepping down next
spring. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CABLE-HITECH _ LOS ANGELES _ Executives of Turner, Cox and
Scientific Atlanta are all prominent at the Western Show where the
theme is the convergence of cable TV technology with the Internet.
A growing number of cable TV operators such as Cox Communications
are using their new digital networks to provide Internet access at
high speeds. (Haddad, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   NORTEL-DEAL _ Atlanta IPO lawyer, John Yates, brokered the $3.25
deal in which Nortel Networks bought Qtera of Boca Raton. The
largest technology deal in the past several months, the acquisition
brings Nortel it's own optical network equipment maker. It also
makes Yates a ton of money. Qtera is a start up with no revenue
that Yates has been working with for 15 months. He usually takes
equity in a company in lieu of retainer, so.... (Clothier, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   QTERA _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Nortel and Qtera have agreed on
a number, a very large number for their deal: $3.25 billion. The
local partners and some managers and employees own 35 percent,
making them very, very rich young people. Their share amounts to
more than $1.1 billion. The rest goes to the venture capital
people. (Pounds, Palm Beah Post).
</P>
<P>
   RECYCLING _ AUSTIN, Texas _ JD Porter has a big idea: Build an
industrial park that will be centered around an operation that
recycles used computer parts. Called an eco-industrial park, the
idea has been tried in Europe and other parts of the U.S., but not
here. It may sound far fetched, but Porter has some pretty big
backers already. (Park, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   CFN-CEO _ ATLANTA _ Q&AMP;A with Cathy Rafelli, CEO of Atlanta-based
Consumer Financial Network (CFN) which began life as an IXL
subsidiary and now has moved into the consumer sector with
YouDecide.com, a financial services Web site. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RAFELLI-BIOBOX _ Bio Box for Cathi Rafelli, president and CEO of
Consumer Financial Network and You Decide.com, two Atlanta-based
financial services sites that help consumers chose auto home or
life insurance as well as mututal funds. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICAN-SHOPPERS _ SAN MARCOS, Texas _ More and more Mexicans
are coming to Texas to shop. The holiday season brings visitors
from across the border, where prices are higher and selection is
not as good. (Pletz, Austin American-Statesman) WITH PHOTOS. Eds:
Moving in both International (i) and Financial (f) categories.
MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   BIZMAGS _ A rundown of the week's financial press. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ADSL _ PUC arbritrators have ruled in favor of two companies,
Covad and Rhythms, that are marketing DSL services and complained
that Southwestern Bell wasn't playing fair. The arbitrators have
largely agreed with Covad and Rhythms and ordered Southwestern Bell
to make changes. Southwestern Bell has appealed the arbitrators'
ruling to the full, three-member commission. This action comes as
the PUC prepares to try to decide again on Thursday whether
Southwestern Bell should be allowed into the long-distance
business. (Hight, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
