<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-LINE _ Atlanta Falcons assistant coach Art Shell has
no idea why the Falcons' offensive line has become like a revolving
door. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).FOOTBALL/COLLEGESFBC-HERITAGE-QB _ ATLANTA _
Participating in the Heritage Bowl will be a homecoming of sorts
for Hampton quarterback Roy Johnson. Johnson was a standout
quarterback at Redan High in DeKalb County and will lead Hampton
into Saturday's McDonald's Heritage Bowl against Southern
University. (Reese, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-PIONEER-RB _ ATLANTA _ Last year, Tuskegee running back
Michael Scott did not make the All-SIAC team and he took out his
frustrations by rushing for 100 yards and scoring a touchdown in
the team's Pioneer Bowl victory over Livingstone. This year, Scott
has returned to the Pioneer Bowl - this time as an all-conference
running back. (Reese, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-ECU _ East Carolina's football team is headed to the Mobile
Alabama Bowl having blocked nine kicks this season, most of which
have been in big games. (Greenville Daily Reflector)
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   BKN-LAKERS _ ATLANTA _ The Los Angeles Lakers make their one and
only appearance in Atlanta this year playing their best basketball
of the season. New coach Phil Jackson appears to have all of the
pieces in place with center Shaquille O'Neal dominating the middle
and guard Kobe Bryant, who recently returned from injury, providing
scoring from outside. The team picked by many experts to advance to
the NBA Finals this season appears to be livio their
preseason billing. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   MISCELLANEOUSSTATE-TITLE _ SEALY, Texas _ Motorists heading west
of I-10 might get a jolt of confusion about 40 miles from Houston.
Rand McNally would indicate they're approaching Sealy. A giant
billboard stationed at the city limit proclaims they're entering
Titletown, Texas. Of course, anyone with even a mild interest in
Texas high school football knows they're one and the same. And if
any uninformed traveler is driving slow enough to read the entire
sign they will understand the double intentity. Sealy won Class 3A
state football championships in 1978, 1994, 1995, 1996 and 1997 and
the town wants everyone to know. Except for its volume of
championships, Sealy isn't much different from any other Texas town
that wins it all. You get the trophy. You get the ring. You get the
billboard. But why is a football championship so important to Texas
communities? Why is a football crown a school's most cherished
prize? (Buchanan, Austin American-Statesman). 35. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GREAT-MOMENTS _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Over the last 100 years sports
have provided some of the most vivid and heartfelt memories for the
state. As the century winds down, what better time to relive the
magical moments that happened in Texas sports? Starting today,
we're counting down the 100 Big as Texas moments in sports in the
past 100 years. We're doing it 10 numbers at a time for the next 10
days. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
