A0059 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-FBC-HERITAGE-QB16-COX     12-15 0503
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-HERITAGE-QB16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Richardson's fall of discontent
 &HT;    By Earnest Reese
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Southern University coach Pete Richardson refers to
the Georgia Dome as a second home for his team. After five
consecutive appearances in the McDonald's Heritage Bowl, Richardson
should feel at home in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   But as Richardson arrives in Atlanta for Saturday's game, he's
not a happy camper. He has already voiced his displeasure over
playing Hampton, which finished third in the Mid-Eastern Athletic
Conference, but he's also upset with the new championship game
format in the SWAC established by commissioner Rudy Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Southern won the first SWAC title game over Jackson State 31-30
last weekend in Birmingham, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   ``The way things are set up now, the only thing our conference
has to look forward to is the McDonald's Heritage Bowl,'' he said.
``If things had been different, I think Jackson State would've gone
to playoffs. But we drew nearly 47,000 in Birmingham Saturday, so I
don't think our championship is going to change.
</P>
<P>
   ``What we need to come up with is a plan where you've got a
better representation of both conferences in the bowl.''
</P>
<P>
   Richardson said he would not be opposed to having the bowl
showdown between a member of the SWAC against a MEAC member at the
beginning of the season rather than the end.
</P>
<P>
   ``You may not have the conference champions because a team may
lose 25 seniors, and wouldn't be the same team,'' he said. ``But a
committee could choose the best representative from both
conferences. It would probably be more exciting at the beginning of
the season.''
</P>
<P>
   Such as matters are, the SWAC has no automatic berth in the I-AA
playoff. To qualify for such a berth, a conference must have all of
its games played the week before the opening round of the playoffs.
Southern and Grambling face each other annually in the Bayou
Classic on the same day the playoffs start.
</P>
<P>
   It would not be economically feasible for those schools to
change that game, since it generates more than a million dollars
for each program compared to mere expenses derived from a playoff
appearance.
</P>
<P>
   And the SWAC championship has virtually ruled out an at-large
berth to the playoffs. Conversely, the MEAC gets an automatic
playoff bid, and the past few years has had a team receive an
at-large berth, also.
</P>
<P>
   That was the case several weeks when conference champ North
Carolina A&AMP;T represented the league in the playoffs and knocked off
top-seeded Tennessee State before losing to Youngstown State.
Florida A&AMP;M also made the field and beat Appalachian State and Troy
State before last weekend's 27-24 loss to championship game-bound
Youngstown State.
</P>
<P>
   All of this talk from Richardson and his displeasure with the
game hasn't gone unnoticed by Hampton coach Joe Taylor.
</P>
<P>
   ``It makes us kind of look forward to this game a little more,''
Taylor said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
