   (NYT27) UNDATED -- Dec. 15, 1999 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT -- The best
way to dislodge a block in the drainpipe is mechanically. For this
you'll need a few basic tools: a plunger, an auger and a few
wrenches. Every homeowner should have a plunger on hand. The best
type of plunger is a funnel-type one with a flexible extension
tube. The tube is designed for plunging a toilet, but it can be
folded back into the cup to plunge sink drains. (Edward R.
Lipinski/The New York Times) LITE
