<P>
   (NYT24) UNDATED -- Dec. 15, 1999 -- BOOK-TALK -- Best-seller
lists have been signaling a return to collected letters. Part of it
is publishers' sensing a millennium-ending bittersweetness about
the past as we speed toward the eventual. Part is that obviously
the pleasures of gossip, voyeurism and intimacy have never left us,
but the only way to get intimate details is in a letter or a
conversation, and conversation disappears. (Tony Cenicola/The New
York Times)
</P>
