   (NYT22) NEW YORK - Dec. 15, 1999 -- LIFTING-JUPITER -- Iron
worker Jerry Ford positions a model of the planet Jupiter at the
Rose Center for Earth and Space at the new Hayden Planetarium on
Wednesday. Refurbishment of the planetarium, which first opened in
1935, is expected to be completed early next year. A sphere, whose
diameter will measure 70 feet, will appear to float inside the new
cubic, glass-walled building. The top half of the sphere will be
the site of one of the most technologically advanced Sky Theaters
in the world: a Virtual Reality planetarium. (Fred Conrad/The New
York Times) LITE
</P>
